         <abstract>Yusuf Salim (1929-2008) was a jazz musician and composer who began his career in Baltimore in the 1940s.  He moved to Durham, North Carolina in the 1970s where he taught jazz workshops through the Salaam Cultural Center and hosted a series on WUNC-TV.  The collection contains manuscripts of 36 lead sheets for Salim's jazz compositions, a piece of prose by Salim, and a photocopy of an article about him from the Raleigh News and Observer.</abstract>
